logical connection between aws private environment and on-prem or another cloud infra using public internet
can be HA if you design it properly
can be setup with in onehour unlike direct connect
VGW: logical gateway you create and associate with a single vpc, this is on aws, from where your datacenter traffic connects
CGW: logical config on aws or physical device that this config refers, this refers to the customer side 
router, or firewall.
let us assume that you are connecting to a datacenter of your organisation
cgw refers to the routr in your datacenter
the vgw is a gateway that is created and attached to the vpc that your onprem network wants to connect
this vgw is the point where your onprem traffic enter